race.comment: SANTORINI SUN (4) settled well back last start but warmed up late to grab third over 1000m at Cloncurry just 10 days ago. Strong run last time and is capable of taking this out. LE FORCE (1) built on a nice third two starts back at this track with a win over 1450m here three-and-a-half weeks ago, getting home by 4 lengths. Has the ability to build on that fine effort last start. TAKERU (8) got the prize two runs ago but was not as effective last time out when sixth over 1000m at this venue, beaten 8 lengths. In contention this time. NAPOLEON STRIKE (6) has been about the mark in recent outings, the latest offering a second over 1200m at Cloncurry a week-and-a-half ago. Must include.
